description:
Per-enricher workers need to claim only their own jobs. Currently enrichment_jobs has one row per SBOM and ClaimNextEnrichmentJob uses SKIP LOCKED with no enricher filter — if two per-enricher workers compete, only one processes each SBOM. Adding enricher_name gives each worker its own independent queue.

WHAT TO DO:
1. Read db/migrations/00034_enrichment_jobs.sql to understand the table shape.
2. Create db/migrations/00036_per_enricher_jobs.sql:
   -- +goose Up
   ALTER TABLE enrichment_jobs ADD COLUMN enricher_name TEXT NOT NULL DEFAULT 'all';
   ALTER TABLE enrichment_jobs ADD CONSTRAINT enrichment_jobs_sbom_enricher_unique UNIQUE (sbom_id, enricher_name);
   CREATE INDEX idx_enrichment_jobs_enricher_queued ON enrichment_jobs (enricher_name, created_at) WHERE state = 'queued';
   -- +goose Down
   DROP INDEX IF EXISTS idx_enrichment_jobs_enricher_queued;
   ALTER TABLE enrichment_jobs DROP CONSTRAINT IF EXISTS enrichment_jobs_sbom_enricher_unique;
   ALTER TABLE enrichment_jobs DROP COLUMN IF EXISTS enricher_name;
3. Read db/queries/enrichment_jobs.sql. Update:
   - InsertEnrichmentJob: add enricher_name to INSERT and params (use @enricher_name::text).
   - ClaimNextEnrichmentJob: add AND enricher_name = @enricher_name::text to the WHERE clause of the CTE and subselect.
4. Run: flox activate -- bash -c 'export PATH="$HOME/go/bin:$PATH"; make generate'
   Confirm internal/repository/enrichment_jobs.sql.go regenerated with EnricherName field in InsertEnrichmentJobParams and ClaimNextEnrichmentJobParams.
5. Read internal/service/job.go. Update struct or calls that build InsertEnrichmentJobParams or ClaimNextEnrichmentJobParams to pass EnricherName. Existing code that uses enricher_name='all' should keep working. EnrichJobClaim struct gains EnricherName string.
6. flox activate -- bash -c 'export PATH="$HOME/go/bin:$PATH"; make build && make test' — must be green.

ACCEPTANCE: make generate && make build && make test green; migration has new column and constraint; sqlc params include EnricherName.
